squidCallToDeprecatedMethod%"@Deprecated" code should not be used"MINOR*java2CallToDeprecatedMethod:÷<p>Once deprecated, classes, and interfaces, and their members should be avoided, rather than used, inherited or extended. Deprecation is a warning that the class or interface has been superseded, and will eventually be removed. The deprecation period allows you to make a smooth transition away from the aging, soon-to-be-retired technology.</p>

