cppIfStatementWithoutBraces"If-else statements must use braces"MAJOR*cpp2IfStatementWithoutBraces:Ë<p>
The statement that forms the body of an if statement or else clause, shall be a compound statement (enclosed within braces), even if that compound statement contains a single statement.
</p>

<p>
The following code snippet illustrates this rule:
</p>

<pre>
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

int main(int argc, char* argv[])
{
  int i;

  /* This if is bad, braces are missing */
  if (i == 0) printf("i == 0!\n"); /* Noncompliant */

  /* This if is bad, braces are missing for the else-clause */
  if (i == 0)
  {
    printf("i == 0!\n");
  }
  else printf("i != 0\n"); /* Noncompliant */

  /* This if is fine */
  if (i == 0)
  {
    printf("i == 0!\n");
  }
  else
  {
    printf("i != 0\n");
  }

  return 0;
}
</pre>

