abapS1067%Expressions should not be too complex"MAJOR*abap:Ω<p>The complexity of an expression is defined by the number of <code>AND</code>, <code>OR</code>, <code>XOR</code> and <code>EQUIV</code> operators it contains.</p>
<p>A single expression's complexity should not become too high to keep the code readable.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<p>With the default threshold value of 3</p>
<pre>
IF ((condition1 AND condition2) OR (condition3 AND condition4)) AND condition5.
  ...
ENDIF.
