abapS1501~To "SELECT", "INSERT" or "DELETE" several lines in databases internal tables should be used in place of loop control structure"CRITICAL*abap:õ<p>Whenever more than one line needs to be read, inserted or deleted from a database table, it is more efficient to work with an internal table than to read, insert or delete the lines one by one inside a loop.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
LOOP AT TAB INTO TAB_WA.
  INSERT INTO CUSTOMERS VALUES TAB_WA.
ENDLOOP.
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
INSERT CUSTOMERS FROM TABLE TAB.
</pre>
