abap:S1671˛
abapS1671EMass operations should be used with internal tables instead of a loop"MAJOR*abap:ö<p>When several lines must be inserted/updated into an internal table, instead of doing those changes line by line, mass operations should be used instead as they offer by design better performances.</p>
<p>This rule checks for single line operation like <code>APPEND</code>, <code>CONCATENATE</code>, and <code>INSERT</code> on internal table in loops. </p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
LOOP AT ITAB1 INTO WA. 
  APPEND WA TO ITAB2. 
ENDLOOP.
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
APPEND LINES OF ITAB1 TO ITAB2. 
</pre>
