abap:S1672ã
abapS16729Sort fields should be provided for an internal table sort"MAJOR*abap:≥<p>Internal tables can be sorted without specifying the specific fields on which to sort. However, doing so is inefficient because when a sort key is not specified, the entire row is used in the sort, which can be markedly inefficient.</p>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
SORT ITAB BY LAND WEIGHT.
</pre>
Á

abap:S1673ÿ
abapS1673@An internal table should be sorted before duplicates are deleted"MAJOR*abap:˘<p>Calling <code>DELETE ADJACENT DUPLICATES</code> won't reliably do any good if the table hasn't first been sorted to put duplicates side by side, since the <code>ADJACENT</code> part of the command looks for multiple rows side-by-side with the same content.</p>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
SORT ITAB BY LAND.
DELETE ADJACENT DUPLICATES FROM ITAB COMPARING LAND.
</pre>
