cS17623"#pragma warning (default: ...)" should not be used"MAJOR*c2S1762:Ø<p>
  Using "#pragma warning (default: ...)" resets the warning in question to its default settings, which may not be what the compiler was initially invoked with.
  Typically, this usage is seen after a warning is turned off, in preparation for code that is known to cause warnings.
  Instead, the warning's current state should be saved, and then restored after the code in question.
</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

