cS23231Line-splicing should not be used in "//" comments"CRITICAL*c2S2323:±<p>
  Line-splicing occurs when the \ character is immediately followed by a new-line character.
  If the source line containing a <code>//</code> comment ends with a \ character in the source character set, the next line becomes part of the comment.
  This may result in unintentional removal of code.
</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
