cS883`Tests of a value against zero should be made explicit, unless the operand is effectively Boolean"MAJOR*c2S883:®<p>Where a data value is to be tested against zero then the test should be made explicit. The exception to this rule is when data represents a Boolean value, even though in C this will in practice be an integer.</p>

