  <li>MISRA C:2012, 17.4 - All exit paths from a function with non-void return type shall have an explicit return statement with an expression</li>
  <li><a href="http://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/394.html">MITRE, CWE-394</a> - Unexpected Status Code or Return Value</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/x/goCGAg">CERT, MSC37-C</a> - Ensure that control never reaches the end of a non-void function</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.securecoding.cert.org/confluence/x/ZoCKC">CERT, MSC36-CPP</a> - Value-returning functions must return a value from all exit paths</li>
