cobolS1740TArithmetic expressions and scalar functions should not be used in "WHERE" conditions"CRITICAL*cobol2S1740:é<p>
Using a scalar function or an arithmetic expression in a <code>WHERE</code> condition can prevent the database 
from using indexes on the relevant column(s), and could therefore lead to performance issues.
</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
SELECT * FROM MY_TABE WHERE C2 = C3 + :HostVar1  -- Noncompliant

SELECT * FROM MY_TABLE WHERE YEAR(BIRTHDATE) > 2000  -- Noncompliant
</pre>
