cobol:S1969Õ
cobolS1969/Section names should be unique within a program"CRITICAL*cobol2S1969:Û<p>
The name of each section should be unique within a program because section names cannot be qualified.
Often code with duplicate section names will not compile.
When it does, sections with duplicate names are ignored, meaning those sections are dead code.
Even if dead code were not an anti-pattern on its own, having two sections with the same name will
inevitably lead to maintenance mistakes.
Therefore duplicative section names should be changed, or the extra sections should be removed.
</p>
