cobolSQL.CursorClosedInsideLoopCheck+"CURSORs" should not be closed inside loops"MAJOR*cobol2SQL.CursorClosedInsideLoopCheck:Û<p>You should avoid closing a <code>CURSOR</code> inside a <code>PERFORM</code> statement, because it could impact performance or lead to unexpected behavior if the cursor was not opened in the same loop.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
 PERFORM UNTIL (NOT DA-OK)
       OR (Y00CIA-CD-RET-PGM = ZERO)
    EXEC SQL CLOSE C2
    END-EXEC
  END-PERFORM.
</pre>
