'cobol:SQL.CursorOpenedMustBeClosedCheckÅ
cobol!SQL.CursorOpenedMustBeClosedCheck*Explicitly opened cursors should be closed"MAJOR*cobol2!SQL.CursorOpenedMustBeClosedCheck:˜<p>If you do not explicitly close a cursor, it will be closed at the end of the task. But if you try to re-open this cursor to process it, you will get an error. That is why a cursor should be explicitly closed after it has been processed.</p>
