cobolSQL.DistinctUsageCheck8"DISTINCT" should not be used in SQL "SELECT" statements"MAJOR*cobol2SQL.DistinctUsageCheck:ñ<p>Using <code>DISTINCT</code> in SQL <code>SELECT</code> statements should be avoided. Not only is this command to remove duplicates not efficient, but a <code>SELECT DISTINCT</code> query is frequently a code smell, and indicates that something is not quite right. That is because using the <code>DISTINCT</code> keyword means that redundant data is being pulled from the database and then discarded.</p>
