cobol:SQL.SelectStarUsageCheckÿ
cobolSQL.SelectStarUsageCheckFColumns to be read with a "SELECT" statement should be clearly defined"MAJOR*cobol2SQL.SelectStarUsageCheck:ƒ<p><code>SELECT *</code> should be avoided because it releases control of the returned columns and could therefore lead to errors and potentially to performance issues.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
SELECT * 
       FROM persons 
       INTO newyorkers 
       WHERE city = 'NEW YORK'
</pre>
