    The value of 0 works without specifying unit for length and percentage. There is no difference between
    <code>0px</code>, <code>0em</code>, <code>0%</code>, or any other zero-value. The units are not important because
    the value is still zero. CSS allows you to omit the units for zero values and still remain valid CSS.
</p>
<p>
    It's recommended to remove units for all zero values because these units aren't being used by the browser and
    therefore can be safely removed to save bytes.
