objcS34916Redundant pointer operator sequences should be removed"CRITICAL*objc2S3491:¢<p>By contract, chaining the 'Address of' operator <code>&amp;</code> with the 'Indirection' operator <code>*</code> results in a return to the initial value. Thus, such combinations are confusing at best, and bugs at worst.</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
int *ptr = ...;
int *result1 = &amp;(*ptr); //Noncompliant
int *result2 = &amp;*ptr; //Noncompliant

int value = 4;
int result3 = *(&amp;value); //Noncompliant
int result4 = *&amp;value; //Noncompliant
</pre>

<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
int *ptr = ...;
int *result1 = ptr;
int *result2 = ptr;

int value = 4;
int result3 = value;
int result4 = value;
</pre>

<h2>Exception</h2>
<pre>
No issue is raised when the <code>*</code> or <code>&amp;</code> operators are overloaded or when both operators are not located in
the same piece of code (one being generated by a macro expansion and the other one located in the main source code for instance).
</pre>
