phpS139:Comments should not be located at the end of lines of code"INFO*php:Á<p>
  This rule verifies that single-line comments are not located at the end of a line of code. The main idea behind this rule is that in order to be really readable,
  trailing comments would have to be properly written and formatted (correct alignment, no interference with the visual structure of the code, not too long to be visible)
