rpgS1619<Numeric fields should be defined as odd length packed fields"MAJOR*rpg:Œ<p>
When storing numeric fields using an odd number of digits allows for the sign to be included in the storage area without any wastage of data storage. 
For example the number -1234567, when packed as 7 digits is stored as follows. 
<pre>
1357
246- 
</pre>
thus taking up only 4 data slots. but when packed as 8 characters it uses 5 data slots 
<pre>
02467 
0135-
</pre> 
or when 7 digits non packed it will be stored as 8 data slots, including the sign. 
<pre>
FFFFFFF6 
12345670
</pre>
</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
     D NUMFLD          S              8P 0 
     D NUMFLD          S              7S 0 
</pre>

<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
