rpgS1634:Non-input files should be accessed with the no lock option"MAJOR*rpg:ﬁ<p>
When accessing a non-input-only file with a CHAIN/READx operation, 
the record is locked and becomes inaccessible to the system, and unreadable other programs. 
This is fine if you are about to update the record immediately, 
but if you have data processing to do following the read, it can leave the record unavailable for too long. 
Therefore, non-input files using the <code>CHAIN</code>, <code>READ</code>, 
<code>READE</code>, <code>READP</code>, and <code>READPE</code> operation codes 
should always be accessed with the no lock option, <code>(N)</code>.
</p>

<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>

<pre>
FDDDLJNL7  UF   E           K DISK    INFSR(*PSSR) 
... 
C                   READ      DDDLJNL7
</pre>

<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>

<pre>
FDDDLJNL7  UF   E           K DISK    INFSR(*PSSR) 
... 
C                   READ(N)   DDDLJNL7       
</pre>
