rpgS2202Prototypes should be used"MAJOR*rpg:ÓSpecifying the parameters to a procedure with a <code>PLIST</code> makes that procedure unusable from free-format code. Instead, prototypes should be used - both when defining a procedure and when calling it. They have the additional benefit of allowing you to use keywords such as <code>Const</code> to better-specify how parameters are passed to a procedure. Further, the use of a prototype instead of a <code>PLIST</code> is cleaner and  more consistent with the code required for subprocedures. 

