vbS1318"Select" statements should end with a "Case Else" clause"MAJOR*vb:ƒ<p>
The requirement for a final <code>Case Else</code> clause is defensive programming.
The clause should either take appropriate action or contain a suitable comment as to why no action is taken.
Even when the <code>Select</code> covers all current values of an <code>enum</code>, a <code>Case Else</code> case should still be used because there is no guarantee that the <code>enum</code> won't be extended.
